  "texts": [
    "Specifically for the switch classification task the AUROC, accuracy, precision, TPR, FPR, F1 score, and Area Under the Precision Recall curve (AUPRC) were calculated.",
    "The standard deviation was calculated to indicate the variation in results.",
    "To provide a baseline for comparison two infection markers that are clearly defined within the latest guidelines 14 were separately also used for predicting when switching could be appropriate in each patient.",
    "Specifically, their temperature must have been between 36 °C and 38 °C for the past 24 h and the Early Warning Score must be decreasing, upon which a switch would then be suggested for the rest of that patient's stay.",
    "It was not possible to include every aspect of the guidelines due to many being ambiguous and not recorded within the data."
  ],
